'''''Star Wars Insider'' 38''' is the thirty-eighth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[June]]/[[July]] [[1998]]. This issue is notable as the first issue in which regular writer [[Scott Chernoff]] became Managing Editor.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Prequel Profile]]: Nick Gillard" {{C|by [[Jamie Painter]]}}
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe]]: Drewe Henley" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[The Wonder Column]]" {{C|by [[Anthony Daniels]]}}
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" &mdash; The Passing of a Legend: Archive Goodwin {{C|by [[Peet Janes]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &ndash; Toy Fair, Episode I And the Elusive B'omarr Monk {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"

===Features===
*"[[Pulp Jedi: An Interview with Episode I Star Samuel L. Jackson]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Hollywood hot shot [[Samuel L. Jackson]] tells Scott Chernoff how he turned his dream of joining the ''Star Wars'' universe into a reality.</small>
*"[[I Bent My Wookiee! Celebrating the Star Wars/Simpsons Connection|I Bent My Wookiee! Celebrating the ''Star Wars''/''Simpsons'' Connection]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>A complete rundown of every ''Star Wars'' reference on our favorite animated sitcom. Scott Chernoff gets the scoop from ''Simpsons'' writers and artists on why the Force is with them.</small>
*"[[Among the Clouds: An Audience with Billy Dee Williams]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>''Star Wars'' icon [[Billy Dee Williams]] tells Scott Chernoff how he made [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] so memorable, and talks about his stature as one of the preeminent African-American stars of cinema.</small>
*"[[Top 20 Star Wars Characters|Top 20'' Star Wars ''Characters]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>Jon Bradley Snyder reveals the results of the ''Insider's'' exhaustive reader poll, complete with your quotes about your favorite characters.</small>

